            <!-- Daemon Tab -->
            <section id="daemon" class="tab-content">
                <h1>Background Daemon</h1>
                
                <p>The DevTrack daemon runs in the background, monitoring Git activity and triggering scheduled events.</p>

                <h2>Features</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Process Management:</strong> Start, stop, restart daemon</li>
                    <li><strong>PID File Management:</strong> Track running daemon process</li>
                    <li><strong>Graceful Shutdown:</strong> Clean shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT</li>
                    <li><strong>Signal Handling:</strong> Reload config on SIGHUP</li>
                    <li><strong>Status Reporting:</strong> Detailed daemon status information</li>
                    <li><strong>Log Management:</strong> File-based logging with rotation support</li>
                    <li><strong>Pause/Resume:</strong> Control scheduler without stopping daemon</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Commands</h2>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code># Start the daemon
./devtrack start

# Check status
./devtrack status

# Pause scheduler (keeps git monitoring active)
./devtrack pause

# Resume scheduler
./devtrack resume

# View logs
./devtrack logs

# Stop the daemon
./devtrack stop

# Restart the daemon
./devtrack restart</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h2>Status Output</h2>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code>DevTrack Daemon Status

Status:     RUNNING
PID:        12345
Uptime:     2h 15m
Started:    Fri, 01 Nov 2025 10:30:00 IST
Triggers:   8
Last:       Fri, 01 Nov 2025 12:45:00 IST

Configuration:
  Config:   ~/.devtrack/config.yaml
  Logs:     ~/.devtrack/daemon.log
  PID file: ~/.devtrack/daemon.pid

Scheduler:
  Paused:       false
  Interval:     180 minutes
  Next trigger: 45 minutes

Work Hours:
  Enabled:      true
  Hours:        9:00 - 18:00
  In hours:     true</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h2>Daemon Lifecycle</h2>
                <div class="workflow-box">
                    <ol>
                        <li>User runs <code>devtrack start</code></li>
                        <li>Daemon checks for existing PID file</li>
                        <li>Forks background process</li>
                        <li>Writes PID to <code>~/.devtrack/daemon.pid</code></li>
                        <li>Initializes Git monitor and scheduler</li>
                        <li>Listens for signals (SIGTERM, SIGINT, SIGHUP)</li>
                        <li>Logs activity to <code>~/.devtrack/daemon.log</code></li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Git Integration Tab -->
            <section id="git-integration" class="tab-content">
                <h1>Git Integration</h1>
                
                <p>Real-time Git repository monitoring and commit detection using file system events.</p>

                <h2>Features</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Git Repository Monitoring:</strong> Real-time detection of commits using fsnotify</li>
                    <li><strong>Commit Information Extraction:</strong> Hash, message, author, timestamp, and changed files</li>
                    <li><strong>Post-Commit Hook Installation:</strong> Automatic hook generation for repository setup</li>
                    <li><strong>Configuration Management:</strong> YAML-based config for repositories and settings</li>
                    <li><strong>Multi-Repository Support:</strong> Monitor multiple repositories simultaneously</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>How It Works</h2>
                <p>The Git monitor watches the <code>.git</code> directory for changes using file system events. When a commit is detected:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Extract commit hash using <code>git log</code></li>
                    <li>Parse commit message, author, and timestamp</li>
                    <li>Get list of changed files using <code>git diff-tree</code></li>
                    <li>Create structured <code>CommitInfo</code> object</li>
                    <li>Send to Python via IPC for processing</li>
                </ol>

                <h2>Configuration</h2>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code>repositories:
  - name: automation_tools
    path: /Users/sraj/git_apps/personal/automation_tools
    enabled: true
    project: DevTrack
    ignore: []</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h2>Testing</h2>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code># Test Git monitoring
cd go-cli
go run . test-git

# Make a commit in another terminal
git commit -m "Test commit"

# Watch the output for commit detection</code></pre>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Scheduler Tab -->
            <section id="scheduler" class="tab-content">
                <h1>Scheduler System</h1>
                
                <p>Time-based trigger system that prompts users at configurable intervals and respects work hours settings.</p>

                <h2>Features</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Configurable Intervals:</strong> Set custom prompt intervals (default: 180 minutes / 3 hours)</li>
                    <li><strong>Pause/Resume:</strong> Temporarily pause and resume scheduling</li>
                    <li><strong>Force Trigger:</strong> Manually trigger prompts on demand</li>
                    <li><strong>Skip Next:</strong> Skip the next scheduled trigger</li>
                    <li><strong>Work Hours Support:</strong> Optional restriction to work hours only</li>
                    <li><strong>Statistics:</strong> Track trigger count and timing</li>
                    <li><strong>Dynamic Interval:</strong> Change interval without restart</li>
                    <li><strong>Cron-based:</strong> Uses robust cron scheduling library</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Configuration</h2>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code>settings:
  prompt_interval: 180  # Minutes between prompts (default: 3 hours)
  work_hours_only: false  # Only trigger during work hours
  work_start_hour: 9   # Start of work hours (24h format)
  work_end_hour: 18    # End of work hours (24h format)
  timezone: Asia/Kolkata  # Timezone for work hours</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h2>Commands</h2>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code># Pause scheduler
devtrack pause

# Resume scheduler
devtrack resume

# Force trigger now
devtrack force-trigger

# Skip next trigger
devtrack skip-next

# Send daily summary
devtrack send-summary</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h2>Work Hours</h2>
                <p>When <code>work_hours_only: true</code>:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Triggers only fire between <code>work_start_hour</code> and <code>work_end_hour</code></li>
                    <li>Outside work hours, triggers are skipped</li>
                    <li>System calculates next work start time</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <!-- IPC Tab -->
            <section id="ipc" class="tab-content">
                <h1>IPC Communication</h1>
                
                <p>Inter-Process Communication enables the Go daemon to communicate with the Python AI layer using Unix sockets or named pipes.</p>

                <h2>Architecture</h2>
                <div class="architecture-diagram">
                    <pre>
┌──────────────────┐         IPC          ┌──────────────────┐
│   Go Daemon      │◄──────────────────►│  Python Bridge   │
│                  │  Unix Socket /      │                  │
│  - Git Monitor   │  Named Pipe         │  - NLP Parser    │
│  - Scheduler     │                     │  - Task Matching │
│  - IPC Server    │                     │  - Ollama AI     │
└──────────────────┘                     └──────────────────┘
                    </pre>
                </div>

                <h2>Message Format</h2>
                <p>All IPC messages use JSON format with newline delimiters.</p>

                <h3>Commit Trigger</h3>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code>{
  "type": "commit_trigger",
  "timestamp": "2025-11-08T10:30:00Z",
  "id": "commit_1699437000000000",
  "data": {
    "repo_path": "/path/to/repo",
    "commit_hash": "abc123...",
    "commit_message": "Fixed login bug",
    "author": "developer@example.com",
    "timestamp": "2025-11-08T10:30:00Z",
    "files_changed": ["src/auth.go", "tests/auth_test.go"],
    "branch": "main"
  }
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h3>Timer Trigger</h3>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code>{
  "type": "timer_trigger",
  "data": {
    "timestamp": "ISO8601",
    "interval_mins": 180,
    "trigger_count": 5
  }
}</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h2>Communication Flow</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Go daemon detects event (commit or timer)</li>
                    <li>Serializes event to JSON</li>
                    <li>Sends over Unix socket to Python bridge</li>
                    <li>Python receives and parses JSON</li>
                    <li>Processes with NLP/AI systems</li>
                    <li>Updates external platforms</li>
                    <li>Sends response back to Go (optional)</li>
                </ol>
            </section>

            <!-- Personalized AI Tab -->
            <section id="personalized-ai" class="tab-content">
                <h1>Personalized AI Learning</h1>
                
                <p>DevTrack's Personalized AI feature learns from your communication patterns across MS Teams, Azure DevOps, and Outlook to generate responses that sound like you.</p>

                <h2>What It Learns</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Writing style:</strong> Sentence structure, complexity, and tone</li>
                    <li><strong>Response patterns:</strong> How you respond to different types of messages</li>
                    <li><strong>Vocabulary:</strong> Words and phrases you commonly use</li>
                    <li><strong>Sign-offs and greetings:</strong> Your typical email/chat closings and openings</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Privacy & Consent</h2>
                <div class="info-box">
                    <h3>Privacy-First Design</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>All data stored locally in <code>~/.devtrack/learning/</code></li>
                        <li>No cloud services or external API calls</li>
                        <li>Uses only local Ollama for AI processing</li>
                        <li>Explicit user consent required before ANY data collection</li>
                        <li>Full data deletion option when revoking consent</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <h2>Quick Start</h2>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code># Enable learning (will prompt for consent)
devtrack enable-learning

# Check consent status
devtrack learning-status

# View your learned profile
devtrack show-profile

# Test response generation
devtrack test-response "Can you review my code?"

# Revoke consent and delete data
devtrack revoke-consent</code></pre>
                </div>

                <h2>Data Sources</h2>
                <h3>MS Teams</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Chat messages where you responded to someone</li>
                    <li>Captures the trigger (what they said) and your response</li>
                    <li>Analyzes conversation context</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Azure DevOps</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Comments on work items</li>
                    <li>Responses in discussions</li>
                    <li>Code review feedback</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Outlook</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Email replies (extracts your response vs quoted text)</li>
                    <li>Subject lines you write</li>
                    <li>Email signatures and greetings</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>How It Works</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Data Collection:</strong> Collects last 30 days of communication samples</li>
                    <li><strong>Pattern Analysis:</strong> Analyzes writing style, vocabulary, and response patterns</li>
                    <li><strong>Profile Building:</strong> Creates your personalized communication profile</li>
                    <li><strong>Response Generation:</strong> Uses local Ollama AI to generate responses in YOUR style</li>
                </ol>

                <h2>Storage Location</h2>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <pre><code>~/.devtrack/learning/
├── consent.json    # Your consent preferences
├── samples.json    # Communication samples
└── profile.json    # Your learned profile</code></pre>
                </div>
            </section>

